Overview

The smallest and most affordable crossover offered here by Peugeot is the 2008. Based on the compact 208 hatchback, it competes with models like the Honda HR-V, Ford EcoSport and Toyota Rush. This French high-rider is offered here in a single variant with a starting price of RM116,578. 

The powertrain that is found under the hood of the 2015 Peugeot 2008 is a direct-injected 1.6-litre inline four-cylinder petrol mill coupled to a six-speed auto adaptive automatic transmission with Tiptronic and Sport mode. This powertrain is good for sending 122hp at 6,000rpm and 160Nm of torque at 4,250rpm to the front wheels. Fuel consumption on the combined driving cycle is rated at 6.5-litres per 100km. 
